Your audio assets can be grouped together from the IDE so they can be loaded and unloaded into memory as required by your game. You can create these audio groups from the Audio Groups window - which can be opened from the Tools menu at the top of the IDE - and you can assign your audio assets to a specific group from the Sound Properties Window.
